<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>


	<ThingDef ParentName="KurinCombatApparelNoColorBase">
		<defName>Kurin_SpaceSuit</defName>
		<label>kurin deep space suit</label>
		<description>A high-tech protective suit for use in space or deep sea environments, relying on a special charging mechanism to regulate internal temperature and pressure. This design allows the suit to instantly harden the impacted areas using a charging mechanism, ensuring it does not sustain serious damage even under great impact. The internal life support system can also collect sweat and other bodily fluids to complete an internal circulation, maintaining the user's life. Kurin users will tuck their tails inside the internal space of the suit - although this is not very comfortable.
This model utilizes Ultra tech, with installed metallic muscle fibers and special servos to automatically perform some simple tasks. The suit's battery can also run in standby mode for up to 10 years...This may sound cool, but if you see a Kurin skeleton wrapped in this thing, laboring away in some abandoned starship, you might not think so.</description>
		<graphicData>
			<texPath>KurinMeowEdition/Item_Apperal/Spacer/SpaceConstructionSuit</texPath>
		</graphicData>
		<costList>
			<Steel>30</Steel>
			<ComponentSpacer>2</ComponentSpacer>
			<Plasteel>65</Plasteel>
		</costList>
		<recipeMaker>
			<researchPrerequisite>ShipBasics</researchPrerequisite>
			<skillRequirements>
				<Crafting>10</Crafting>
			</skillRequirements>
			<researchPrerequisites Inherit="false">
				<li>KurinComplexApparel</li>
			</researchPrerequisites>
			<recipeUsers Inherit="False">
				<li>FabricationBench</li>
			</recipeUsers>
		</recipeMaker>
		<techLevel>Spacer</techLevel>
		<thingCategories Inherit="false">
			<li>Kurin_Apparel_Spacer</li>
		</thingCategories>
		<generateCommonality>2</generateCommonality>
		<apparel>
			<developmentalStageFilter>Child, Adult</developmentalStageFilter>
			<bodyPartGroups>
				<li>Torso</li>
				<li>Neck</li>
				<li>Shoulders</li>
				<li>Arms</li>
				<li>Legs</li>
				<li>Hands</li>
				<li>Feet</li>
			</bodyPartGroups>
			<layers>
				<li>Kurin_Shoes</li>
				<li>Middle</li>
				<li>Shell</li>
			</layers>
			<tags>
				<li>Kurin_Spacer</li>
				<li>Kurin_SpaceSuit</li>
				<li>HideKurinTail</li>
				<li>Royal</li>
				<li>RoyalTier5</li>
			</tags>
			<defaultOutfitTags>
				<li>Worker</li>
			</defaultOutfitTags>
			<wornGraphicPath>KurinMeowEdition/Item_Apperal/Spacer/SpaceConstructionSuit</wornGraphicPath>
		</apparel>
		<statBases>
			<Mass>7</Mass>
			<Flammability>0.3</Flammability>
			<WorkToMake>17500</WorkToMake>
			<MaxHitPoints>350</MaxHitPoints>
			<EquipDelay>6.0</EquipDelay>
			<ArmorRating_Blunt>0.4</ArmorRating_Blunt>
			<ArmorRating_Sharp>0.75</ArmorRating_Sharp>
			<ArmorRating_Heat>0.75</ArmorRating_Heat>
			<Insulation_Cold>150</Insulation_Cold>
			<Insulation_Heat>50</Insulation_Heat>
		</statBases>
		<equippedStatOffsets>
			<ConstructionSpeedFactor>0.15</ConstructionSpeedFactor>
			<ResearchSpeed>0.1</ResearchSpeed>
			<FixBrokenDownBuildingSuccessChance>0.15</FixBrokenDownBuildingSuccessChance>
		</equippedStatOffsets>
		<comps>
		</comps>
	</ThingDef>


	<ThingDef ParentName="KurinCombatApparelNoColorBase">
		<defName>Kurin_SpaceHelmet</defName>
		<label>kurin deep space helmet</label>
		<description>A high-tech protective helmet for use in space or deep sea environments, relying on a special charging mechanism to regulate internal temperature and pressure. This helmet has heat radiation tracking and thermal imaging functions, both integrated into the protective faceplate's optical sensors. When not in use, the sensors need to be manually raised. Kurins jokingly refer to this bulky helmet as the "goldfish bowl", with the expansive starscape and the hopeful eyes of aerospace pioneers etched onto its somewhat hazy faceplate.</description>
